British High
Commissioner Jane Marriott is rooting for dialogue between investors and the Nandi
County government to resolve the long standing dispute over the multinational
tea farms and the Kerebe gold mines. Speaking after
meeting Nandi Governor Stephen Sang in Kapsabet, Marriott acknowledged the
wrong doings of the British colonial rule. She also vouched
for stronger relations between Kenya and Britain in various sectors including
agriculture, health, and tourism that continue to benefit the citizens of both
countries. On his part,
Governor Sang welcomed the willingness of the British government to resolve the
disputes to create a win-win situation between the two parties.  Marriott was in
Nandi to launch a conflict resolution blueprint sponsored by the British
government to assist the conflict prone areas of North Rift region.